# Investigation 003 - Windows Host Port Scan

## Date
2026-03-30

## Objective
Scan the Windows host machine from Kali Linux to identify
open ports and assess potential attack surface.

## Tool Used
Nmap 7.98

## Scan Command
sudo nmap -sV 192.168.56.1

## Open Ports Discovered
| Port | Service | Version |
|------|---------|---------|
| 135/tcp | Windows RPC | Microsoft Windows RPC |
| 139/tcp | NetBIOS | Microsoft Windows netbios-ssn |
| 445/tcp | SMB | Microsoft-DS |
| 5432/tcp | PostgreSQL | PostgreSQL DB 9.6.0+ |
| 8000/tcp | HTTP | Uvicorn (Python) |

## Risk Analysis
- **Port 445 (SMB)** — High risk if internet facing. 
  Exploited by WannaCry ransomware in 2017.
- **Port 5432 (PostgreSQL)** — Database exposed on network.
  Should be bound to localhost only.
- **Port 8000 (Uvicorn)** — Python web server running.
  Likely a development project.

## Conclusion
No immediate danger as these ports are only visible within
the local VirtualBox network and not exposed to the internet.
However in a real corporate environment ports 445 and 5432
would require immediate attention and hardening.

